The following Terraform code has a critical error. The `spot_instance_request` block inside the `aws_launch_template` resource is invalid and will cause a Terraform plan failure.
1.  What is the correct argument to use within an `aws_launch_template` to specify that instances should be Spot Instances?
2.  Please provide the corrected code snippet for just the `aws_launch_template` resource.
Code with error:    resource "aws_launch_template" "default" {  
name_prefix = "sample-lt-"  
image_id = "ami-0c55b31ad2299a701"  
instance_type = "t3.micro"
tag_specifications {  
resource_type = "instance"  
tags = {  
Name = "sample-asg-instance"  
}  
}
# **THIS BLOCK IS WRONG AND WILL FAIL**
spot_instance_request {  
type = "one-time"  
}  
}
